cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a cognitive architecture for detecting affordances in the visual modality using a real-world mobile robot. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) techniques for detecting affordances. The use of a hierarchical training process and simulation approach also suggests that the paper may belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-categories.
